data.title: Cloud & Carrier Providers
data.meta_description: With a focus on adaptability and advanced technologies, our Cloud and Carrier Services empower businesses to navigate the digital landscape with confidence.
data.text:
8x8, Inc. is the number one provider of unified communications and collaboration (UCC) services in the cloud for Mid-Market and Distributed Enterprises. 8x8 offers the most reliable network available with a global footprint, easy deployment and full service customer support.

Offering a cost-effective, reliable alternative to complex, on-premise phone systems, 8x8's Virtual Office, Virtual Office Pro and Virtual Contact Center meet the critical performance requirements of your customers. Call recording, virtual faxing, built-in security compliance (including HIPAA, SOX and FISMA) and disaster-preparedness functionality supports the growing demands of today's mobile, BYOD, anytime/anywhere work environment.

Award winning AireSpring is one of the fastest growing telecommunications carriers in the USA, with over 6 billion call records processed every year. AireSpring is a privately held, diversified, debt free, and full service communications company which offers a broad range of innovative services at competitive prices.

AireSpring offers next-generation Integrated, SIP/VoIP, Voice, Data, Cloud Hosted IP PBX, MPLS and Conferencing products geared to deliver power and flexibility at cost-effective rates.

Appgate, Inc. is a secure access company providing solutions for people, devices and systems based on the principles of Zero Trust. Appgate secures more than 1,000 organizations across 40 counties supported by more than 500 employees. Last year alone, Appgate mitigated more than 11 million online threats. Appgate was spun out of Cyxtera Technologies on Jan. 1, 2020, and on average, most Appgate product suites and IP have been helping clients improve their security posture for over 5 years.

Established in 1950, Arvig has grown from a small, family-owned telephone company to one of the largest independent telecommunications providers in the nation with over 700 employee-owners.

Arvig's over 3,500 route miles of fiber in Minnesota stretches from northern Minnesota, through Minneapolis/St. Paul, to southern Minnesota, near the Iowa border. Arvig also has a construction division that builds all of their own fiber and can offer greater control of the customer's experience, especially when a fiber build is required.

Arvig owns and operates 14 rural LEC territories in Minnesota, and sprinkles in CLEC territories in the remainder of the state with customers in 45 of Minnesota's 87 counties.

AudioCodes has a wide variety of advanced voice networking and media processing products and solutions for the digital workplace. We operate in over 100 countries, 6 continents, with follow the sun support. We are the voice partner for your customers, no matter what they need or where they are.

We’re often referred to as the “One Voice” company – that’s because we offer the full solution, end to end. This means one vendor for devices, applications, logistics, support, and professional services. One suite of management tools for voice network lifecycle management. We have solutions that your business need.

Avaya is a global leader in digital communications software, services and devices for businesses of all sizes. Our open, intelligent and customizable solutions for contact centers and unified communications offer the flexibility of Cloud, on-premises and hybrid deployments. Avaya is the market share leader in small and midsize telephony with over 600,000 customer deployments and 26 million users relying on Avaya's market proven, award winning IP Office solution that has been delivering rich communications to small and midsized customers for over 15 years.

Avaya Holdings Corp. is traded on the NYSE under the ticker AVYA. For more on all of Avaya's offerings, please visit www.avaya.com or for more information on Avaya Cloud IP Office visit www.avayamarket.com.

As a communications and technology solutions leader since 1994, BCN understands how to solve your toughest network challenges and build a solution that fits your needs. Our experts guide you to the right solution, then help you secure, manage, and monitor it, ensuring you’re always connected to the advanced technologies that can take your business even further.

With over 75 network and technology partnerships and an unshakable commitment to delivering exceptional customer care, your business gets access to best-in-class services and an experience that is second to none. A privately held company, BCN serves a growing roster of customers nationally and internationally. Contact BCN at 1.888.866.7266 or email: Simplicity@bcntele.com for more information.

BIO-key is a trusted provider of Identity and Access Management (IAM) and Identity-Bound Biometric solutions that offer an easy and secure way to authenticate the identity of employees, customers, and suppliers while managing their access across devices and applications. Over 1,000 global customers, including AT&T, the federal government, and 200+ higher education institutions trust BIO-key PortalGuard IDaaS, an award-winning IAM platform, to reduce password-related help desk calls by up to 95%, eliminate passwords, secure remote access, prevent phishing attacks, and improve productivity for the IT team. PortalGuard provides the simplicity and flexibility required to secure the modern digital experience with options for single sign-on, self-service password reset, and over 16 multi-factor authentication methods, and is the only IAM platform to offer Identity-Bound Biometrics. Backed by decades of expertise, BIO-key has a proven track record of successful IAM project delivery and strong customer relationships.

Atlantic Broadband, a subsidiary of Cogeco Communications Inc., is the 9th largest cable operator in the United States. Let us partner with you to provide the speed, flexibility, and reliability of a fiber data & voice network, backed by the responsive, personal service your business depends on. Regardless of the size or type of business you have, we have a business communications solution that works for you. From professional services and retail to bars and restaurants, we can help your industry.

PUT PARTNERSHIP TO WORK.

Whether it’s an Internet and Phone Bundle, a custom Fiber solution or a range of other services, we’re here to help you find the right business communications solution for you.

International network connectivity is our core strategic focus, and we are a group of international consultants in terms of DIA, P2P, MPLS, IP Transit and SD-WAN etc. We have been growing strategically and expansively across the globe and because of the infrastructure we have established worldwide, we are able to provide customers with a one-stop shop experience in addition to the most cutting-edge technologies offered to Enterprise customers. Either it is equipment procurement or managed services, international connectivity & voice, or cloud connections with mainstream cloud providers, we are proud to offer exclusiveness and innovation integrated with network foundation and a superior customer service supported by our NoC globally. We are always your advocates and reliability is what makes us successful.

At Cirion, we provide you with a comprehensive set of digital infrastructure and technology  solution that suit your customer needs and goals.

Cirion is a leading digital infrastructure and technology provider, with presence in 20 countries, offering a comprehensive suite of fiber network, connectivity, colocation, cloud infrastructure, and communication and collaboration solutions with the purpose of furthering Latin America’s progress through technology.

Cirion serves over 6,400 Latin America-based and multinational customers, including enterprises, government agencies, cloud service providers, wireline and wireless carriers, ISPs, and other leading businesses.

Cirion owns and operates a facilities-based network with 31k miles of terrestrial fiber network, 23k miles of subsea network and 18 data centers spanning across the Latin America region. Cirion is committed to delivering positive customer experience, from sales to service activation and network operations. It offers customized solutions that meet the specific requirements and expectations of its customers.

The Consolidated Communications, Inc. (CCI) Agent Program gives you freedom and benefits, and gives your customers what they need; reliable telecom products and services with a teamed approach. Our Agent Program is an easy way for you to create new revenue for yourself and your company.

Our program is designed specifically for consultants, system integrators, inter-connect, agents, and cabling companies with a small to medium customer base and an active sales force. When you become an CCI Agent, your customers get enhanced, reliable voice, Internet, and messaging service at a great price. And you get an ongoing revenue stream you can count on.

At CCI, we know it can be difficult to navigate the ever-changing needs of your customers. That’s why CCI provides you with the most comprehensive and reliable support channel in the industry.

Core BTS is a customer-centric technology consulting organization dedicated to transforming IT experiences and delivering value to clients.

Our team has more than 25 years of experience and holds top-level certifications with Microsoft, Cisco, VMware, EMC, and Citrix that allow us to provide our customers with expertise across multiple technologies. In addition to our top-tier partnerships, Core BTS holds many partnerships with other national and regional technology providers to ensure we can provide our customers with a holistic technology solution.

Core BTS has over 2,500 active customers across industries including, healthcare, education, financial services, and manufacturing. Although Core sells IT products, we take a vendor agnostic collaborative approach to designing the right project that provides the most value to our clients - we lead with IT assessments.

Dialpad is an AI-powered phone system that connects your entire organization across one, cloud-based platform through voice, video, messaging and meetings across all devices.

Dialpad Support is the cloud-based service platform built for Support Orgs. With Dialpad Support, Agents can integrate with existing support tools to deliver exceptional customer service with each interaction.

Dialpad Sell is the cloud-based sales platform built for sales teams. With Dialpad Sell, Sales Managers get the full picture of their pipeline, thanks to native integrations with sales and coaching tools.

Uberconference is an enterprise web conferencing solution that offers voice, video and messaging which integrate into the productivity tools you use everyday. With Uberconference, meetings are effortless allowing your teams to focus on collaboration with their teammates or customers.

Effortless is an innovative Cloud and Security Provider, which migrates entire business infrastructures into the cloud. Effortless customers are businesses around the world that increase efficiency and save money by utilizing the solutions tailored to their business needs. Effortless brings customers into the cloud with a customized FlightPlan. They start with an IT audit; then, a private cloud is built using ClearSky Environment Technology. When the cloud has been tested and approved, Effortless migrates clients' desktops, servers, applications, and the entire business network into the Effortless Cloud. Clients and their staff access this via high-level encryption from almost any Internet-enabled device.

Equinix is the world’s digital infrastructure company. We interconnect industry-leading organizations in finance, manufacturing, mobility, transportation, government, healthcare and education across a cloud-first world.

Founded in Silicon Valley in 1998 as a vendor-neutral multitenant data center provider where competing networks could securely connect and share data traffic, we chose a name that reflected our company’s focus on EQUality, Neutrality and Internet eXchange—Equinix. And we began building the global platform our customers would need to make digital business happen: Platform Equinix®.

Today our 220+data centers in 60+ markets on five continents connect enterprises, networks, services and innovators from Mumbai to Dublin, Singapore to Chicago, and Helsinki to San José. Digital leaders worldwide harness our trusted platform to bring together and interconnect the foundational infrastructure that powers their success.

Thousands of leading enterprises have a presence in our global data centers, putting new opportunities with service providers, partners and customers within easy reach. Whether you’re building a history-making product, blazing an industry-first business model or pioneering a new way to collaborate globally, Equinix provides the global reach, the rich ecosystem and the service excellence today’s enterprises need to compete and win.

EXA Infrastructure is a leading provider of digital infrastructure services with a core focus on data transport to, from and within Europe. We own and operate a portfolio of assets across 34 countries that include the most route miles of any carrier in Europe, three wholly owned subsea Trans-Atlantic cables, dense European metro footprints, cable landing stations in key markets, and a fleet of data centers. Our customers include some of the world's largest and most demanding organizations, and the company is headquartered in London, England.

FiberLight is a Georgia-headquartered company with 20 years of experience in creating networks for some of the most exacting customers. As one of the largest private fiber companies, we’re committed to organic growth of our footprint, offering networking options in custom solutions at layers 1, 2, and 3 to major commercial hubs throughout the country. FiberLight owns over 1,600,000 miles of robust fiber networks in over 100 US cities and towns within Florida, Georgia, Maryland, Texas, Virginia, and Washington, DC.

Since 2008, First Orion has transformed the phone call experience for businesses, carriers and consumers through its industry-leading communication branding and protection solutions. The global telecommunications solutions provider helps companies to generate more revenue, increase efficiency, and improve the customer experience by empowering them to brand their phone calls with their name and reason for calling. First Orion also provides the industry’s most secure calling experience and best-in-class analytics for call program optimization resulting in a higher contact rate and a positive impact to ROI for any enterprise, vertical or use case. As the market leader in branded calling, First Orion is a trusted partner to Fortune 500 companies and the largest U.S. mobile carriers. For more information, visit firstorion.com.

First Communications is a leading technology solutions provider offering data networking, voice, and managed services throughout the Midwest. Founded in 1998, First Communications network has grown to include more than 600 on-net wire centers and supports over 35,000 customers.

Headquartered in Akron, Ohio and a 24x7x365 Network Management Center in Chicago, First Communications is dedicated to pairing effective customer communications with next generation technology.

We create solutions to align with your business objectives, while our built-in scalability accommodates for the future. Combined with a strong focus on the customer experience and operational expertise, First Communications bridges technology with world class customer service.

Flexential, which was formed in late 2017 through the merger of Peak 10 + ViaWest, is deeply invested in the success of its 4,200+ customers, who trust it to deliver core data center solutions of colocation and connectivity, as well as DRaaS, compliant private and public cloud and professional services. Flexential has 41 highly redundant and connectivity-rich data centers featuring more than 3 million square feet of data center space across 21 markets focused in the US and Canada. Flexential helps organizations optimize their journey of IT transformation while simultaneously balancing cost, scalability, compliance and security. Flexential has a customer first focus as evidenced by its industry leading NPS score of 67.4, which places it in best-in-class providers.

Globalgig is a provider of global, hyper-connectivity solutions with a primary focus on cellular wireless data connectivity. Whether the use case is resilient wireless connectivity for a SD-WAN deployment, wireless connectivity for an Internet of Things initiative, or wireless connectivity for construction trailers, we have your customers covered from America to Argentina, Australia, Austria, and beyond. We can do just the SIM and Service as well as provide a turnkey solution with a Cradlepoint router and is fully managed from install through operation. We do not bind your customer to any single Mobile Network Operator (MNO) but rather use the optimal MNO?s network for each location. Many verticals, such as Retail, are best served by aggregated connectivity so we have also developed the capability to aggregate the wired connectivity into a single global wired and wireless connectivity solution. We are fast, easy to work with, and consistent.

STOP leaving the door WIDE open for your competition, and STOP leaving valuable income on the table.

Before and during the installation of carrier or host services, many businesses have onsite survey, onsite cabling, or deployment needs. After carrier or host services have been installed, many businesses require 24x7x365 Managed Services, 24x7x365 Centralized Help Desk Services and SLA Onsite Maintenance to ensure that their Data and Voice WAN, WLAN and LAN are up and remain healthy!

Welcome to Global Onsite.

Global Onsite is a multi-vendor, multi-technology, IT services organization providing CHANNEL ONLY lifecycle professional, onsite, and remotely managed network services for Voice and Data WAN, LAN, WLAN and “near network” solutions. Our portfolio of services perfectly complements those professional organizations that serve the enterprise and mid-markets by providing a single sourced solution for ‘the rest of’ their clients network service’s needs.

Our most successful relationships are with Consultants, Integrators and Agents that focus on selling Carrier and Cloud Services, but seek to provide a more robust suite of solutions to their valuable clientele. It’s those organizations that understand ‘somebody’ is benefiting from caring for a client’s network both before and after the network is dropped – and if its THEM, they will slam the door shut on future competition by being a much larger part of their networks ongoing support and maintenance.

Our Services can be more fully reviewed at www.globalonsite.com. Don’t hesitate to call us today and discuss how we can serve your organization.

At GoTo, we believe flexible-work software should lift you up, not weigh you down. That’s why we make communication & collaboration, IT management, and support tools that make it easy for you to do your best work, wherever. Solutions built for IT and ideal for SMBs, designed to help you reclaim your time, freeing you up to do the things you need, so you have more time to do the things you want. We’re here to ensure the time you work is well-spent, so your time outside work can be better spent.

GTT Connects People – Across Organizations, Around the World and to Every Application in the Cloud

GTT is redefining global communications to serve a cloud-based future, connecting people across organizations, around the world and to every application in the cloud. Our clients benefit from an outstanding service experience built on our core values of simplicity, speed and agility. A Fortune Future 50 company, GTT owns and operates a global Tier 1 internet network and provides a comprehensive suite of cloud networking services to any location in the world.

iNET is a privately held and debt free communications company offering a full range of services. iNET was founded on the premise that competitive pricing doesn't need to compromise customer service or creative solutions. iNet's mission is to provide the communications services you need with the customer service you deserve. iNET values its relationships with its customers, suppliers, agents, partners, and employees and enforces the ethics and accountability that foster and strengthen those relationships. The iNET engineering team with decades of combined experience employs a consultative approach that allows them to adapt to the changing needs of our customers.

Intermedia Cloud Communications helps over 125,000 businesses connect better from wherever. We eliminate the need for multiple communications service providers with our seamlessly integrated solutions portfolio – including voice, video, chat, contact center, business email, productivity, and file management – delivered on one highly reliable, secure platform. With one monthly bill, one point of control, and six-years running J.D. Power-certified support, Intermedia provides enterprise-grade products with a Worry-Free Experience.

And as a partner-first company, we provide everything partners need to help maximize their revenue and success through our innovative, highly supported agent and reseller channel programs.

Intrado Helps You See the Big Picture, Turning Information to Insight

Intrado operates at the center of digital engagement, enabling companies to better connect with customers, stakeholders and employees, using technologies that propel them through an inevitable digital transformation.

Intrado offers the industry’s largest and most complete UCaaS, CCaaS and enterprise safety services portfolio – including our own proprietary solutions as well as those from Cisco, Microsoft and other leading technology vendors.

With operations that span the globe, Intrado can provide a scalable single-vendor solution with simplified ordering and deployment for organizations in the midmarket through large enterprise. We’re experienced deploying in complex environments and we can support a hybrid cloud approach.

The CASCADE platform is an award-winning pioneer for the distribution of cloud services from the biggest cloud software vendors in the world, including Microsoft, Acronis and Symantec. CASCADE's self-service portal and the original Cloud Marketplace, enables partners to seamlessly order and manage cloud services for their clients 24/7. The platform and proposition are unique, in that it allows resellers of any kind whether they are proficient in IT Sales and Support or not, to service their existing client base. CASCADE is globally recognized for leading the way in cloud distribution and supporting partners in maximizing the opportunity in their chosen industry.

iTel is a converged network company that harnesses the power of every carrier and every technology, which enables us to create an affordable network solution for any sized business in even the most difficult locations across the country. As a business-focused provider, we dedicate 100% of our efforts to servicing business clients. This means we have the expertise and ability to create customized solutions for every company's needs. iTel's partners are the foundation of our business, we understand that their success is our success too. We have recently revamped our Partner Program to create the best-possible experience for everyone in our Channel.

Joonto is a revolutionary platform the brings together the power of mobile phone metrics for B2B customers, and is the first-ever SIM/(eSIM)-as-a-Service platform to automatically track, manage, and monitor ALL mobile phone call and text activity on user’s secondary business line, along with the capabilities of integrating all mobile phone activity within user’s CRMs, ERPs, and other data sources through real-time API integrations. Joonto offers a new take on enterprise telephony by enabling users and teams the ability to unleash the full potential of both UCaaS and CCaaS through user's device eSIM/SIM card directly. No more need for utilization of soft phone or VoIP apps, but instead Joonto has created a platform designed to empower all users with the full capabilities of enterprise telephony through a mobile device's native operating system.

Lumen is the third largest telecommunications company in the United States. The company provides broadband, voice and wireless services to consumers and businesses across the country. In addition, the company provides data, voice and managed services to business, government and wholesale customers in local, national and select international markets through its high-quality advanced fiber optic network and multiple data centers. Lumen is recognized as a leader in the network services market by key technology industry analyst firms. Lumen's customers range from Fortune 500 companies in some of the country's largest cities to families living in rural America. Headquartered in Monroe, La., Lumen is an S&P 500 company and is included among the Fortune 500 list of America's largest corporations.

A leading integrated technology service provider with national clients. Designated as a Copier Dealer, MSP/MSSP, CSP, VAR and System Integrator. Professional Services spanning from assessments, planning, discovery and design through installation and support, we apply our network expertise to voice, data, video, print and security solutions.

Expect Satisfaction, we've been conducting monthly, annual and on demand customer surveys and documenting results since 1994, to ensure we meet your expectations.

Caring and committed, we believe it's not enough for a business to do well; it must also do "good." On the job and off, Marco is made up of people who care.

Innovation Leader, when you connect with Marco, you benefit from the innovation and resources of our industry leading partners.

Get your customers to the cloud. Fast!

On-demand scalable connectivity to hundreds of Cloud and Network Service Providers, data centres, and enterprises.

Megaport is transforming the way people, enterprises, and service providers interconnect across the globe. Our Software Defined Network (SDN) enables customers with fast, flexible, and on-demand connectivity to any services on the Megaport Ecosystem. We have an extensive footprint throughout Asia Pacific, North America, and Europe where customers can access the Network from 240+ locations. Our world-leading connectivity solution drives greater agility, reduced operating costs, and increased speed to market compared to traditional connectivity options.

Mitel is the business communication experts powering more than 2 billion connections every day, including over 33 million daily cloud connections. We help companies connect, collaborate and take care of their customers anywhere, anytime, over any device. With over 40 years of experience providing business communication solutions, more than 60 million users in 100 countries have entrusted us with their communication needs. It?s why we hold the #1 market share leader in Europe, the Middle East and Africa and why Garter has recognized us as a Leader in Unified Communications. And offering the best path to the cloud has made us the fastest-growing global cloud communication provider in the world. Powering more than 2 billion connections every day, Mitel (NASDAQ: MITL; TSX: MNW) helps businesses connect, collaborate and take care of their customers. That includes more than 33 million cloud connections daily, making Mitel the world?s fastest growing provider of cloud communications. Our business communications experts serve more than 70 million users with over 2500 channel partners in more than 100 countries. We have #1 market share in EMEA and have been identified by top industry analyst firms as a business communications leader. For more information, go to www.mitel.com and follow us on Twitter @Mitel

Nord Security was born as a passion project, and their drive is reflected in their work, which has earned high praise from major tech outlets and cybersecurity experts. They want one thing only — to provide true online privacy and security at an affordable price to as many businesses as they can with cloud native solutions that provide our partners with a zero-day sales cycle to execute on what were previously complex solutions.

Today, nearly 7,000 businesses use Nord Security products. NordLayer provides a cloud native solution for SASE and ZTNA, ensuring businesses worldwide have secure network access security, while NordPass and NordLocker are quickly gaining recognition in the tech world for protecting passwords, shared credentials, and files respectively. In less than a decade, they have grown from just 4 passionate friends to 2,000+ cybersecurity experts — and they’re not stopping anytime soon.

The Cloud Communications Division of NTT Ltd., (formerly known as Arkadin) is a leading Global Collaboration Service Provider, offering a complete range of hybrid workplace solutions including contact center, direct routing/voice plans for Microsoft and Cisco Teams, and hosted global hybrid digital events. Across the Americas, EMEA, APAC and more, we help enterprises accelerate the use of unified communications services to streamline business productivity through platform optimization, change management, support and adoption, confidently enabling the connected future for every employee. Clients trust us to analyze and consolidate their existing suite of communication tools into one global solution, for a holistic and smarter way of working; delivering benefits back to their businesses with greater agility, improved customer and employee experience, and compelling ROI. NTT Cloud Communications fully supports Intelisys sales partners through our channel program.

RagingWire Data Centers, Inc. designs, builds, and operates mission critical data centers that are ideal for high-growth cloud/software companies as well as established Fortune 1000 enterprises.

The company has 113 MW of critical power spread across 1.5 million square feet of data center infrastructure in Northern California (near the Bay Area and Silicon Valley), Ashburn, Virginia (the #1 data center market in the world), and Dallas, Texas (the #2 data center market in the U.S.). In addition, RagingWire is actively developing data center properties in these locations and other top North American data center markets.

RagingWire solutions deliver 100% uptime, high-density power/cooling, extensive multi-layered facility security, carrier neutral connectivity, and superior customer service. Typical configurations span from single racks to secured cages with 5-10 racks and dedicated multi-megawatt suites.

As part of the NTT Communications group, RagingWire is one of the largest data center providers in the world with a global network of 140 data centers in 19 countries and one of the most financially strong companies in the data center industry.

Altice combines the fiber-rich network coverage and services of Optimum, Lightpath and Suddenlink to offer customers expanded solutions from a single, proven provider. Whether you are seeking to implement next-generation networks, access new markets, or enhance current performance, you can rely on our growing, high-capacity network. With local access services to a significant number of lit buildings via fiber and coax plant, we can help connect you to the buildings you want.

Our 100% end-to-end, fully -owned fiber-optic network now covers over 19,500 route miles across multiple states including hard-to-reach rural areas and the dense NYC area. (NY, NJ, CT, WV, NC, TX, OK, LA, MO, AR, CA, NV, OH, WV)

Carrier-grade network architecture delivers the high performance and availability your customers depend on. We continue to invest in our network infrastructure to support the ongoing success of our customers and partners.

State-of-the-art NOCs provide an additional level of network protection and support 24/7/365.

Playvox enables companies to transform their customer service operations into a hub of efficiency, effectiveness and engagement by integrating the CRM platform. Easily forecast, schedule and plan out various scenarios for optimal capacity to minimize wait times and delight customers. Improve agent productivity by providing real-time metrics and eliminate context switching. Identify trends and prioritize the data reviewed, while also motivating and engaging agents through recognition and badges. Playvox empowers the workforce to drive stronger customer experiences.

Generate a more accurately forecast, automatically.

Optimize scheduling – without overstaffing

Gain real-time operations management.

Track metrics and easily identify insights

Playvox's powerfully simple workforce engagement management (WEM) solutions transform customer care. We deeply understand that exceptional employee engagement produces extraordinary customer experiences, and we love creating tools that help our customers unlock the full potential in every employee and every interaction. Playvox powers the world's fastest-growing brands.

Shaw Business has the scale to meet connectivity solutions now and into the future with a Fibre network of over a million kilometers, top tier-speeds and enterprise grade technology. Shaw Business offers a multitude of solutions including, Broadband Internet, Data, SD WAN, Voice and TV.

Whether it’s a reliable Internet connection for direct payment transactions or incredible speed for day-to-day file transfers, count on Shaw Business to deliver what you need, when you need it. Shaw Business provides industry leading speeds, a superior network with a plan for any size business, dependable connections, and unlimited data.

For more than 20 years, SilverSky has partnered with thousands of customers across multiple industries to bring them cybersecurity that’s effective. Over the years, they have continuously evolved and strengthened their services to help customers stay secure and compliant in a changing world – just as cybercriminals have continuously grown in their sophistication, attack surfaces have become more extensive, and regulatory compliance demands have become more stringent. SilverSky levels the playing field for companies of all sizes with the most comprehensive managed detection and response (MDR) solution in the industry. Critical cybersecurity service areas are backed by leading security technologies and highly skilled security operations and cybersecurity experts. Delivered as a managed services model, SilverSky MDR helps customers address their modern and ever-changing risk with a solution that makes powerful, enterprise-grade cybersecurity simple, affordable, and accessible.

Skywire Networks is one of the most active and fastest growing Ethernet providers in New York City with more than 500 lit buildings, 35 hubs, and a near-net footprint of 30,000+ commercial buildings. We provide SLA, fiber class throughput and connectivity to thousands of businesses in NYC. We sell our services directly to end-users, through agents and channel partners and to wholesale partners via NNI connectivity. We sell Ethernet Private Lines, Internet Services and hosted voice services to both enterprise businesses and SMB’s at speeds ranging from 10mb to 10gb. Skywire Networks addresses the problem of poor fiber density in NYC in a multitude of ways by leveraging various edge technologies including Fiber and Fixed Wireless Access.

Sprinklr is the leading enterprise company for all customer-facing functions. With advanced AI, Sprinklr's unified customer experience management (Unified-CXM) platform allows enterprises to listen to, reach, and engage with their customers on over 30 channels. We help companies deliver human experiences to every customer, every time, across any modern channel.

90% of customers want immediate responses to their questions, but most contact centers can’t keep up. Sprinklr Service is the first purpose-built Contact Center as a Service (CCaas) that ensures you and your agents can offer frictionless support. It scales customer service across 30+ digital and traditional channels — including voice — with self-service systems, AI bots, and one unified view of the customer.

For more information on Sprinklr, you can visit our products page below:

https://www.sprinklr.com/products/

TailWind is a premier nationwide service provider that delivers “always on” connectivity to remote locations, complete with end-to-end solutions spanning both sides of the demarcation point. And although we remain headquartered in Minneapolis, Minnesota, we serve more than 40,000 locations across North America.

In today’s global economy, connectivity isn’t merely a convenience — it’s a necessity. TailWind takes complete accountability for all aspects of your business network as your dedicated partner. We guarantee your ability to conduct business anytime and anywhere, and we’re devoted to providing first-class management of your assets, service, and connectivity issues. We’re committed to addressing the unique challenges multi-location businesses face and ensuring that our customers benefit from lowered costs, increased reliability, seamless scalability, and reduced risks.

At TailWind, we understand how difficult it can be to keep up with the rapidly evolving technology landscape, yet you can count on us to help you cut through the noise. From infrastructure to sourcing carrier services, we manage every project for every branch through completion. And, we’ll stay by your side as you grow to ensure your network is ready for the future.

​​​​​​​With over 20 years of experience in the hospitality vertical RealCom Solutions has the proven track record as a trusted advisor to hotel ownership and management groups across the US. Our team of hospitality experts know the specific hotel franchise standards and our leadership team has put together an impressive list of partners approved for all the major hotel franchises. This allows us to provide you the approved solution for any of your hotel technology needs. Our dedicated business development, project management, and service management teams will work with you closely throughout the entire process to ensure a successful installation, opening and ongoing support of the hotel. 

Telefonica is one of the world's largest fully integrated, Tier 1, telecommunication providers. We have presence in 45 countries, with full operations in 18 countries. We serve multinational businesses – especially those that have a presence in Latin America or Europe.
